# Yemen Flow Hub Backend Rules

Read `../AGENTS.md` before taking any action. It is the single file of truth.

## Git
Backend code lives in two repos. After every change, commit to both:
1. `backend/` → `git@github.com:ultimate-eg/yemen-flow-hub-backend.git` (team repo)
2. Root `/` → `git@github.com:majedsiefalnasr/yemen-flow-hub.git` (monorepo, `git add backend/<files>`)

Commit format: `type(scope): description`
Never add or commit generated artifacts from `graphify-out/`, `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/`, or `_bmad-output/test-artifacts/`. Keep them local only.

## Stack
PHP 8.2+, Laravel 11, Sanctum, MySQL, Redis

## Non-negotiable Architecture Rules

### WorkflowService is the only path for status changes
```php
// ✅ Correct
$workflowService->transition($request, 'support_approve', $user);

// ❌ Never
$request->current_status = RequestStatus::SUPPORT_APPROVED;
$request->save();
```

### Thin controllers
Controllers only: receive request → validate → call service → return response.
Zero business logic in controllers.

### Canonical status enum
Use only these values (from `../AGENTS.md`):
DRAFT, DRAFT_REJECTED_INTERNAL, SUBMITTED, BANK_REVIEW, BANK_APPROVED,
SUPPORT_REVIEW_PENDING, SUPPORT_REVIEW_IN_PROGRESS, SUPPORT_APPROVED,
SUPPORT_REJECTED, WAITING_FOR_SWIFT, SWIFT_UPLOADED, WAITING_FOR_VOTING_OPEN,
EXECUTIVE_VOTING_OPEN, EXECUTIVE_VOTING_CLOSED, EXECUTIVE_APPROVED,
EXECUTIVE_REJECTED, CUSTOMS_DECLARATION_ISSUED, COMPLETED

### Visibility scoping
All Eloquent queries for requests must scope by `bank_id` for bank users.
Never return requests outside a user's organization.

### Audit logging
Every transition → `request_stage_history` record + `audit_logs` record.
`audit_logs` must include: `user_id`, `role`, `action`, `from_status`, `to_status`.

### Voting concurrency
```php
DB::transaction(function() use ($request, $vote) {
    $request->lockForUpdate()->find($request->id);
    // validate session still open, then record vote
});
```

### Immutable state responses
```php
// Terminal states return 403
return response()->json([
    'success' => false,
    'message' => '...',
    'error_code' => 'WORKFLOW_IMMUTABLE_STATE',
    'current_status' => $request->current_status,
], 403);
```

### File uploads
PDF only. Private storage. `SWIFT_UPLOADED` documents are immutable after upload.

